plot: Tony gets sick from food poisoning and blames Artie's restaurant. Pussy, meanwhile, reaches the end of the line.

Meadow's graduation is finally at hand and she decides on which college to attend. Tony is having something of a rough time with a severe bout of food poisoning. In his sick bed, he has interesting dreams about those around him. He also finds Pussy's wire so they go fishing along with Sylvio and Paulie. Pussy won't return. Tony is arrested at home when his mother Livia and her sister are stopped at the airport with stolen airline tickets. At Meadow's graduation, Tony has a final chat with David Scatino, the man whose gambling debts to Tony and Richie Aprile led to his ruin.—garykmcd

After a meeting with Paulie and Silvio, Tony goes home and goes to sleep, only to wake up ill and vomiting from food poisoning, which he blames on Artie Bucco. As he drifts in and out of consciousness, he has mysterious dreams that appear to give him visions about the people around him, including Pussy and Dr. Melfi. When he stops by Pussy's house later to invite him to check out a new boat, Tony discovers indisputable proof that Pussy has been informing to the FBI, and the boat trip becomes Pussy's last. Soon after Tony, Silvio and Paulie return without Pussy, FBI agents swarm down on the Soprano residence.—Jean-Marc Rocher <rocher@fiberbit.net>
